<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/gre_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/gre_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Superstars, CA 4/28/2002<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(5.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=5659'>Philip "I Jedi" Green</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=5659&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> May 4, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> These reports chronicle my adventures and attempts to destroy<br>
The One Ring, and to RULE them all....<br>
<br>
Chapter II<br>
In the middle<br>
<br>
This is the tale of my first sealed deck booster draft. It picks up where my first story ended.... Well in the end I placed 3rd which I was very happy with. David Kemner took 1st and I&#39;m not sure who was 2nd, it was Steve Daniels or Marius Kiciski. In my three packs of MoM I pulled Mithril-Coat, No Mere Ranger, A Promise, a foil Must Do Without Hope and a foil Goblin Bowman for placing 3rd. The Coat will be really nice for playing against Uruk-hai, Moria with weapons, and archery decks. Well that&#39;s it! .... Or was it?<br>
<br>
Indeed it was not. For Steve Daniels, my worthy opponent from game three announced that he would be hosting a sealed deck booster draft on the 28th (just over two weeks away). Four days before the tournament, I bought a Moria Gandalf starter to use as my base deck for the tournament. I played a couple games with it to get accustomed to playing with it and before I know it, Sunday was upon me. My brothers and I head out to Superstars at around 3:30 and arrive shortly there after. I grab a Gimli starter for three bucks minus the rares, just to have it and the drafting begins not long after. I&#39;m placed in a drafting pool with Steve (who is playing so there is no bye) and two others. The draft does not go well for me, but it goes quite well for Steve (to the right of me) and the guy to the left of me. The guy to the left pulls a rare Boromir, a Flaming Brand, a MoM Witch King, and good cards for his Aragorn starter. Steve on the other hand, is laughing his head off (apparently I was passing up cards I shouldn&#39;t have been passing up) on top of that he pulled a foil MoM Witch King, not my day:) Oh well:) On to my deck and the games!<br>
<br>
Deck:<br>
The One Ring, TRR<br>
Frodo, RA<br>
Gandalf, TGP<br>
<br>
The sites from the starter<br>
<br>
Boromir, SOD x2<br>
Merry, FOTB x2<br>
Legolas, POM x2<br>
Fror, GK x2<br>
Barliman Butterbur, PPP x2<br>
Sam, PP<br>
Farin, DE<br>
Gandalf, TGP (in addition to the one I start)<br>
<br>
Wizard Staff x3<br>
Hobbit Sword x2<br>
Armor<br>
SOTWT x2<br>
Mysterious Wizard x2<br>
Strength Of Spirit x3<br>
Intimidate x3<br>
Sorry About Everything<br>
Deft In Their Movement<br>
Wielder Of The Flame<br>
You Cannot Pass!<br>
There And Back Again<br>
<br>
Goblin Pursuer x3 <br>
Goblin Flanker x3<br>
Goblin Scavengers x3<br>
Goblin Spearman x4<br>
Goblin Runner x3<br>
Goblin Backstabber<br>
Goblin Wallcrawler<br>
Goblin Marksman<br>
Goblin Bowman<br>
Moria Scout<br>
The Balrog, DB<br>
Orc Taskmaster<br>
MoM Enquea<br>
<br>
Goblin Spear x4<br>
<br>
Troubled Mountains<br>
Host Of Thousands<br>
<br>
Dark Fire x2<br>
The Long Dark x2<br>
They Are Coming<br>
<br>
Game 1 vs. the guy to the left of me in the draft&#39;s Aragorn/Uruk-hai deck<br>
I bid to go first and I do, I make it to site three only running into an Uruk-hai Soldier, but the one card off the top is Boromir! He gives Aragorn a Coat Of Mail and move into a Spearman with a spear at site two, after Aragorn takes three wounds he stops. I drop Legolas, a Wizard Staff, Fror, and give Merry a Hobbit Sword (I pulled Merry at my site one). I move to site four, the Hollin and find a Raiding Party and a Shaman there. Gandalf looses against the Raiding Party, and Fror takes a wound after Gandalf Intimidates. He moves to site three after playing Boromir SOD. I do not play anything there. I bring Farin into play and move to the Bridge, he played a Soldier and a Savage. Merry and Fror take care of them and I stop. He plays Armor on Boromir and moves to site four, I greet him with a Marksman and a Spearman/Spear. Frodo takes the arrow while Boromir and Aragorn get pumped up to win both skirmishes. I move on to site six, there he cannot bring enough to stop me from healing all my wounds the next turn. He plays Pippin, MT who then gets killed by the Balrog at site five. Boromir took a wound from the Balrog as well. I continue on to site seven where everyone exerts due to the site. He drops a Rager but Gandalf wins against it, thanks to a Mysterious Wizard. He moves to site six where I play an Orc Taskmaster, MoM Enquea, and a Runner. He pumps up Aragorn/Boromir again, so only Frodo takes a wound. I bring down Boromir with Armor and move to site eight, he plays three Uruk-hai, but I do not loose anyone to them. He moves to site seven, there I play two Goblin Scavengers and pull two spears out of my lost pile for them, Boromir and Aragorn both take a wound there so he stops. I move to the final site and face only four Uruk-hai. So Frodo lives and I win.<br>
<br>
Result: FW +3<br>
Total score: +3<br>
Good things: Finding Boromir after loosing one off the top.<br>
Bad things: Nothing really.<br>
<br>
I find out after that game, that Timothy (My younger brother) pulled a Green Leaf Legolas and that Paul (My older brother) pulled the rare Gandalf. Where are my good cards? Like I said &quot;oh well&quot;:)<br>
<br>
Game 2 vs. ??????&#39;s Moria Gandalf deck<br>
I opt to bid zero, so he wins the bid with four and chooses to go first. We both pulled Merry and made the jump to site three. Here&#39;s what our Fellowships looked like, Mine had MoM Gandalf, Merry, and Legolas. His was the same except he had Boromir and Fror instead of Legolas. He gives Merry a Sword and moves to site four where I drop four orcs on top of him (My hand was mostly shadow the whole game), but he makes it through with only a wound on Fror. I give Gandalf a Wizard Staff and move to site four, I find a Pursuer, and a Scavengers with a Spear there. The Pursuer bites it to Archery and Gandalf is wounded by the Scavengers. He plays the sacrificial dwarf ally and then moves to The Bridge. Out comes my Balrog and eats the sacrificial dwarf after Merry used stealth to hide. I follow in his foot steps after bring out Farin. I don&#39;t run into the Balrog but a Fierce Nasgul does pretty much the same thing in a sealed deck tournament. Merry and Fror eat it there, so I stop. He plays Sam, PP and a Dwarf Guard. Then he moves into Enquea, an Orc Taskmaster, and a marksman, but I am unable to do enough damage to prevent him from healing all of his wounds. I move on to the Sanctuary and attempt to regroup. He moves to site seven where I play a Flanker. He assigns Gandalf to fight it and plays Mysterious Wizard to win the skirmish. He choices to move onto site eight, I play another Flanker there, and this time Gandalf takes a wound, as well as Boromir. My free peoples turn, I play as many cards as I can so I will have a better chance of finding more shadow cards. He moves to site nine where I play eight assorted orcs, but Sam saves the day for him&#8230;so I loose.<br>
<br>
Result: FL +1<br>
Total score: +4<br>
Good things: Having a swarm the size that a constructed deck would have at site nine under normal circumstances.<br>
Bad things: Loosing is always a bad thing, but it was a good game.<br>
<br>
Game 3 vs. Timothy Green&#39;s Greenleaf/Moria deck<br>
Timothy bids zero and I bid two, I choose to go first. I pull Merry and make an easy jump to site three. Timothy started Legolas G, Merry, and Pippin. He also makes it easily to site three. I give Gandalf a Wizards Staff and move to the Lake where I exert Frodo. Timothy plays a Scavengers, Pursuer, Scrabbler and a Sneak there. So Frodo gets double teamed and I&#39;m thinking that&#39;s it, but then I remember Gandalf has a Wizard Staff. I exert Gandalf twice to make the sneak minus three strength, so Frodo will live.... Or so I thought, BOOM Drums In The Deep, and Frodo dies at site four.<br>
<br>
Result: FL +1<br>
Total score: +5<br>
Good things: Like what?<br>
Bad things: loosing at site four.<br>
<br>
Game 4 vs. Sean Mcguire&#39;s Aragorn deck<br>
After loosing in a very bad way in the last game, I bid zero and plan on letting my shadow win it for me (I hope). Once again, we both make it to site three easily. He moves to the Lake with just Aragorn and Frodo with a Hobbit Sword. He exerts Frodo and I play three low power orcs, one of them being my only Backstabber. For some reason he leaves the Backstabber to me for assignment, and of course I assign him to Frodo, so Frodo dies. Then I ask him if he wants to see how the game would have ended if he had not done that. So this is what would have happened, I move to my site four and Gandalf kills a Fighter with a new Staff. He moves to site five where I pull the Balrog and it kills both Aragorn and Frodo.<br>
<br>
Result: FW +3<br>
Total score: +8<br>
Good things: Sean is a lot of fun to play, and we talked until the rest of the games were over (which was a while).<br>
Bad things: I feel bad after winning games like that.<br>
<br>
So that&#39;s it, after a 6-way tie for 3rd. I ended in 6th which was a little disappointing, but I did not pull very good. Alfred Dong took 1st with a very powerful fellowship. I believe Steve Daniels was 2nd who also had a good fellowship.<br>
<br>
Props:<br>
Big props to Timothy for trading Legolas Greenleaf to me the next day<br>
To Paul for driving me<br>
To Alfred for the MoM rares he gave me (I have very little MoM)<br>
To Steve Daniels for running the tournament<br>
To Superstars for letting us play there<br>
<br>
Slops:<br>
To my deck for not giving me another companion in game three<br>
<br>
Well that&#39;s it.<br>
<br>
Thanks for reading.                                 <br>
